<br>
I find the security of a much longer mez (dazzle) to be worth any pro's entrance/enthrall might provide.  With dazzle, I have LOTS of time to get things under control.  Basically, once I land it on a mob, I can FORGET about that mez until all the CCing is done.  This is especially helpful on big Hate pulls.  The extra 24 seconds is a huge advantage.  BUT that's my opinion.  When other enchanters use entrance on raids, it annoys the hell outta me..  however, obviously, others are going to prefer entrance, and I'm certainy not going to ask them to change their style for me.  I think in the end, it boils down to not only personal preference, but also necessity for the area in question.  For now, however, entrance remains on page 37 of my spellbook.  Eh.. I digress.. this is another thread in itself.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><img src = http://members.bellatlantic.net/~mezner/daeonsig2.jpg><br>
56th Beguiler<br><b><i>Guildleader</i> of <a href = http://www.eternalsinn.net><i>Eternal Sinn</a></b><br>
</center></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Whore</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/25/01 4:35:09 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~suretang/images/usf2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are you competitive?</span><hr size=1> There is no &quot; better &quot; mezz really than the others...<br>
<br>
What it boils down to, is you should use the mezz that allows for the fewest number of remezzes.  Remezzes = extra agro and extra mana waste.<br>
<br>
If you can entrance, and the mob is killed before you need to remez, you are using the right spell for the job.  If you constantly have to remezz and the mob is killed shortly after, you should use dazzle.<br>
<br>
The recast time on dazzle is a non issue for most enchanters, since you will normally Flux ( or shift ) on a mezz resist anyway.  Dazzle fits inside of flux , even with the recast.  If you play on a lag free connection, you can even flux - dazzle without moving ( ie with the mob in your face ).  If you have lag, you can flux , move 2 steps ( while the spell refreshes ), then dazzle.  In both cases the recast time of dazzle is a non issue.<br>
<br>
<br>
The only reason i use dazzle all the time at present is , frankly because im lazy.  I used to get a feel for where i was, and use the mezz spell that would cover the least remezzes.. if that was entrance / enthrall, thats what i used.. its the most mana efficient way.<br>
<br>
As for GoK and juggs, it depends on how many you get, and what your job duties are , and who you have with you.<br>
<br>
The last 3 times i have been down there it was with one group.  I had a shaman..  Even i can tank a slowed jugg, if i had to, so if there was a three pull, i would rapture one immediately, then root the second.  Tash second, tash first , then root first.<br>
<br>
Keep those 2 rooted ( shaman has slowed them by now ).<br>
<br>
On 2 pulls i would normally rapture one then tash + root if i have a shaman, or Tash + slow + root if i dont.<br>
<br>
In all cases where i say &quot; root &quot; i mean fetter, which i prefer over basic root.<br>
<br>
Ole.. i didnt say all enchanters use entrance to make a point, i say some do.  I dont recall ever working with you, so i wasnt saying you specifically were doing that.<br>
<br>
I would respectfully disagree with the fact that entrance / enthrall is always the best spell , however.  Dazzle allows the control of larger trains as well /shrug.<br>
<br>
<br>
EDIT : i would not reccomend for an enchanter to switch to dazzle as a primary mezz until level 53-54 or so, when you have C2 and Theft of thought, and also several levels to get the bonus on casting spells under your level.  Dazzle ( all spells actually ) are a bitch to channel when you first get them...<br>
<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.mithrilweb.com//"target="web"><img src="http://www.mithrilweb.com/images/sigs/llosig.jpg" border="0">

