<BR><A HREF="http://www.mischief-n-mayhem.com/">Mischief~n~Mayhem</A>
</CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uguurn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Guurn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/26/01 7:45:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are you competitive?</span><hr size=1>   I solo chant almost all of our raids so there are few instances for me to try to outdo another enchanter.  Even so, I wouldn't try.  If we were in one of the rare places that a raid could overpull badly I wouldn't care who was first, I want to live.  There really aren't that many places that more require alot of mezzing (5+ mobs in camp).  Other than Hate, Fear, and Chardok I honestly can't think of any. <br>
